		<ns0:id>http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/1171</ns0:id><ns0:author>
			<ns0:name>jamesfen...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105008541472586726939/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Support for user supplied main() function in nacl applications provides highest level of flexibility and make porting of QT/FLTK and other GUI applications much easier.
By encouraging users to use Module/Instance/Paint_Manager paradigm in PPAPI 2, we are losing one of the most important feature in PPAPI 1.

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
PPAPI 1 support user defined main() function, but PPAPI 2 seems not.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
Most GUI applications has their own control flow, to accommodate PPAPI 2 control flow, these applications need some major changes.
If PPAPI 2 continues to support main(), we can easily add an adaptive layer on top of application without changing application itself to port them.
This will make porting GUI applications almost effortless.  

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
PPAPI 2 can expose entry point for main() function.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
User can implement their own message loop in their own main() function.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
We will see much more QT/FLTK applications ported to NACL.
